body_html:
@imaoldboy libtensorflow_demo.so is an optional library, so there is no issue due to it being missing (it only contains object tracking and faster-than-Java image color conversion code written in C).

libtensorflow_inference.so is the one that contains TensorFlow itself. Are you depending on org.tensorflow:tensorflow-android:+ and still seeing this issue? Can you tell what version of the TF native library you're getting?

body:
@imaoldboy libtensorflow_demo.so is an optional library, so there is no issue due to it being missing (it only contains object tracking and faster-than-Java image color conversion code written in C).

libtensorflow_inference.so is the one that contains TensorFlow itself. Are you depending on `org.tensorflow:tensorflow-android:+` and still seeing this issue? Can you tell what version of the TF native library you're getting?
